        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:34PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 434 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles east of Fairfield Lake to Buffalo.
These storms were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Buffalo around 440 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Lanely, Johnson,
Dew, Corinth, Massey Lake, Tennessee Colony, Red Lake, Oakwood, and
Donie.

This includes Interstate 45 between mile markers 174 and 191.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
